#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Explore the Waf build system in Spack, a Python-based tool for configuring "
"and building software projects without Makefiles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:13
msgid "Waf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"Like SCons, Waf is a general-purpose build system that does not rely on "
"Makefiles to build software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:18
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:20
msgid ""
"The ``WafBuilder`` and ``WafPackage`` base classes come with the following "
"phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:22
msgid "``configure`` - configure the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:23
msgid "``build`` - build the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:24
msgid "``install`` - install the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:26
msgid "By default, these phases run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:28
msgid ""
"$ python waf configure --prefix=/path/to/installation/prefix\n"
"$ python waf build\n"
"$ python waf install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:35
msgid "Each of these are standard Waf commands and can be found by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:37
msgid "$ python waf --help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:42
msgid "Each phase provides a ``<phase>`` function that runs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:44
msgid "$ python waf -j<jobs> <phase>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:49
msgid ""
"where ``<jobs>`` is the number of parallel jobs to build with. Each phase "
"also has a ``<phase_args>`` function that can pass arguments to this call. "
"All of these functions are empty. The ``configure`` phase automatically "
"adds  ``--prefix=/path/to/installation/prefix``, so you don't need to add "
"that in the ``configure_args``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:55
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:57
msgid ""
"``WafPackage`` also provides ``test`` and ``installtest`` methods, which are "
"run after the ``build`` and ``install`` phases, respectively. By default, "
"these phases do nothing, but you can override them to run package-specific "
"unit tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:60
msgid ""
"def installtest(self):\n"
"    with working_dir(\"test\"):\n"
"        pytest = which(\"py.test\")\n"
"        pytest()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:69
msgid "Important files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:71
msgid ""
"Each Waf package comes with a custom ``waf`` build script, written in "
"Python. This script contains instructions to build the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:74
msgid ""
"The package also comes with a ``wscript`` file. This file is used to "
"override the default ``configure``, ``build``, and ``install`` phases to "
"customize the Waf project. It also allows developers to override the default "
"``./waf --help`` message. Check this file to find useful information about "
"dependencies and the minimum versions that are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:80
msgid "Build system dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:82
msgid ""
"``WafPackage`` does not require ``waf`` to build. ``waf`` is only needed to "
"create the ``./waf`` script. Since ``./waf`` is a Python script, Python is "
"needed to build the project. ``WafPackage`` adds the following dependency "
"automatically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:87
msgid "depends_on(\"python@2.5:\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:92
msgid "Waf only supports Python 2.5 and up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:95
msgid "Passing arguments to Waf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:97
msgid ""
"As previously mentioned, each phase comes with a ``<phase_args>`` function "
"that can be used to pass arguments to that particular phase. For example, if "
"you need to pass arguments to the build phase, you can use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:100
msgid ""
"def build_args(self, spec, prefix):\n"
"    args = []\n"
"\n"
"    if self.run_tests:\n"
"        args.append(\"--test\")\n"
"\n"
"    return args"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:111
msgid "A list of valid options can be found by running ``./waf --help``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:114
msgid "External documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/wafpackage.rst:116
msgid "For more information on the Waf build system, see: https://waf.io/book/"
msgstr ""
